{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "Soul Machines Interactions API",
    "description": "The Soul Machines Interactions API lets you create fully customized digital person interactions on demand \u2014 programmatically, at scale. Instead of pre-configuring static avatars, you define each interaction's context, purpose, personality, and tone in real time, then receive a unique, shareable URL to deliver that personalized experience to your end users.\n\n### How it works\n1.  **Make an API request** \u2014 Send a JSON payload describing who the digital person should be (avatar, name, role, tone) and what they should do (purpose, context, objectives).\n2.  **Get a unique URL** \u2014 The API responds with a secure interaction link you can embed, share, or open in a browser.\n3.  **Run the session** \u2014 Your end user talks to the digital person. When they finish, you can capture interaction results programmatically.\n\n### Why you'd use it\n*   **Deliver just-in-time personalization** \u2014 tailor conversations for each customer, scenario, or moment.\n*   **Scale without overhead** \u2014 no need to pre-create and maintain hundreds of static configurations.\n*   **Stay in control** \u2014 define goals, tone, and context dynamically to align the AI's behavior with your brand.\n\nThis flexible API-first approach makes it easy to orchestrate rich, personalized digital people experiences while keeping integration and backend logic clean and scalable.\n\nObtain an API key from [Soul Machines Digital Workforce Connect](https://workforce.soulmachines.com/).\n",
    "version": "1.0.0",
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://interactions-api.soulmachines.cloud/openapi.json"
  },
  "paths": {
    "/api/v1/generator": {
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "generator"
        ],
        "summary": "Create Generator Interaction",
        "description": "Generates a new Soul Machines interaction.\n\nThis endpoint is designed to receive specifications for an AI assistant (Digital Person),\nincluding its purpose, context, objectives, and expected results. It then uses an\nLLM (e.g., GPT-4) to generate the necessary system prompts, welcome messages,\nand structured objectives for the interaction.\n\nFor MCP server integration, this endpoint can be used to programmatically create\nand configure new Digital Person interactions/experiences based on predefined templates or\ndynamic inputs. The generated `interaction_url` is the expected output to the user asking to generate an interaction.",
        "operationId": "create_generator_interaction_api_v1_generator_post",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "x-api-key",
            "in": "header",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "title": "X-Api-Key"
            }
          }
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "required": true,
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/GeneratorRequest"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Successful Response",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InteractionSummary"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "422": {
            "description": "Validation Error",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/HTTPValidationError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Bad request"
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized"
          }
        }
      }
    },
